{{E|The Merchant???|2}} is an {{2|Events|Event}} found in the {{2|Hive}} and the {{2|Glory}}. It first appears as a normal {{2|Merchant}} encounter, but instead sells a set of knock-off {{2|Relics}}.

== Relics ==
The fake Merchant's shop only contains a set of 6 Relics, each costing a random amount between 43-57 {{2|Gold}}. The 6 Relics are randomly chosen out of the list below:

* {{R|Anchor???||2}}
* {{R|Blood Vial???||2}}
* {{R|Happy Flower???||2}}
* {{R|Lee's Waffle???||2}}
* {{R|Mango???||2}}
* {{R|Orichalcum???||2}}
* {{R|Snecko Eye???||2}}
* {{R|Strike Dummy???||2}}
* {{R|Venerable Tea Set???||2}}

== Combat ==
If a {{P|Foul Potion||2}} is owned, it can be thrown at the fake Merchant to trigger combat. Winning the combat will give 300 Gold, the ability to take all of the Relics that were for sale, and {{R|The Merchant's Rug???||2}}, which does nothing. Relics can be skipped if they are not wanted, which is most likely to occur for {{R|Snecko Eye???||2}}.

{{Enemy Infobox|The Merchant???|2}}

== Pattern ==
{{Intents|The Merchant???|2}}
* Always uses {{Int|The Merchant???|Swipe||2}} first. 
* {{Int|The Merchant???|Swipe||2}}, {{Int|The Merchant???|Spew Coins||2}}, and {{Int|The Merchant???|Enrage||2}} randomly lead into 1 of the 3 other possible moves 
** Cannot use the same move twice in a row.
* {{Int|The Merchant???|Enrage||2}} can only be chosen once every 3 turns. 
* {{Int|The Merchant???|Throw Relic||2}} is randomly followed up by {{Int|The Merchant???|Swipe||2}} or {{Int|The Merchant???|Spew Coins||2}}.

